Specs for ntpstats files: http://www.eecis.udel.edu/~mills/ntp/html/monopt.html

loopstats (one line for each system clock update)
  0 date
  1 time past midnight
  2 clock offset
  3 frequency offset
  4 RMS jitter
  5 RMS frequency jitter (wander)
  6 clock discipline loop time constant


peerstats (one line for each "NTP packet or reference clock update received")
  0 date
  1 time past midnight
  2 source address
  3 status word
  4 clock offset
  5 roundtrip delay
  6 dispersion
  7 RMS jitter


rawstats (one line per NTP packet received)
  0 date
  1 time past midnight
  2 source address
  3 destination address
  4 origin timestamp
  5 receive timestamp
  6 transmit timestamp
  7 destination timestamp
  8 leap warning indicator
  9  NTP version
  10  mode
  11  stratum
  12  poll
  13  precision
*  14  total roundtrip delay to the primary reference clock
*  15  total dispersion to the primary reference clock
  16  refid, association ID


sysstats (one line per hour)
/* Probably useless */
